My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in systems programming, Unix/Linux environments, and technical problem-solving — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I executed the full development lifecycle of AI research projects on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, managing data preparation, model training, fine-tuning with LORA, and deployment on Pace University's HPC cluster using CUDA, PyTorch, and vLLM. I utilized Unix/Linux commands and shell scripting on HPC cluster environments to automate model training jobs, monitor resource utilization, and troubleshoot deployment issues — directly mirroring the Unix/Linux expertise and systems-level thinking central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, adapts to changing business demands, and creates innovative solutions to complex problems, all of which I would bring to DP World's mission.

I have always been passionate about driving innovation and sustainability in global trade through technology and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of DP World's mission to provide end-to-end supply chain solutions that create value for all stakeholders. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

